<!-- Start Body -->
Generalized anxiety disorder had almost driven me to the point of suicide. I could no longer stand waking up with panic attacks and being freaked out by things that normal people could so easily handle.<br/>
<br/>
I'd been on paxil and urbanol...they didn't really work apart from making me feel sedated. But the anxiety was still there, below the surface.<br/>
<br/>
Now I'm trying bromazepam. It's only been three days but for the first time in my life I can just sit, and chill out, without anxiety coursing through my veins.<br/>
<br/>
It's something so many people take for granted, and now I'm finally experiencing it.<br/>
<br/>
Time will tell whether bromazepan will completely solve my problems, and addiction could be an issue. But for now I'm content being the normal, happy adult I always wanted to be.<!-- End Body -->
<br/><br style="clear:both;"/>


